# Historical Tools & Evolution

## Sweave (2002)

One of the earliest tools that combined R and LaTeX, allowing users to embed code directly within documents for reproducible research @Leisch2002.

## Knitr

Sweave later evolved into knitr, which improved usability, flexibility, and overall performance in generating dynamic reports @Xie2014.

This evolution enabled:

- easier customization  
- better integration of code, results, and narrative text  

